Their wings, a kaleidoscope of sight,

With wings so bright, colors bold,
Butterflies, young hearts to enfold.

Their metamorphosis, beauteous sight,
From cocoon to wing, a wondrous flight.

Their metamorphosis, a wondrous sight,
From cocoon to winged beauty take flight.

Their metamorphosis,  a wondrous sight,
From crawling caterpillar to winged delight.

Their metamorphosis, a wondrous feat,
From crawling worm to winged treat.

Emerging new, A radiant sight,
Unfurling beauty, the world's delight.

Unfurling slowly, their beauty rare,
A symbol hope, beyond compare.

They spread their beauty far and wide,
A symbol of hope,200,side.

With gentle touch, they alight,
Drinking in the sweetest sight.

With gentle touch, they alight on flowers fair,
Drinking in sweetness with each sip they share.

In summer's breeze, they take to flight,
A gentle touch, a wondrous sight.

With gentle touch, they land on flowers fair,
Drinking in the sweetness of the air.

With every flutter, they take to the air,
A whispered promise beyond compare.

For in their wake, we find our own way,
To spread our wings and seize the day.
